🌱Siamese are the best hunting dogs 🤣😭🌱 Have you checked out our #microfarm @mjschookiefarm yet? Please follow for not only farm education, gardening and growing tips, and raising chickens for eggs - but also for rural comfort foods recipes with roots from the #PNW or #Cascadia region. 

By definition, bioregions like Cascadia share a common set of natural characteristics such as animals, plant life, soil, watersheds, climate, and geology.

What is Cascadia? Cascadia is the name for the bioregion of the Columbia, Fraser & Snake River valleys, and includes all of British Columbia, Idaho, Oregon & Washington as well as parts of Northern California, Nevada, Montana, Southern Alaska, Wyoming.

What is Cascadian food? Cascadian cuisine tends to focus on organic and locally harvested fruits, vegetables, meats, & seafood. Apples, blackberries, cherries, wild berries, salmon, crab, locally produced coffee, backyard chicken eggs, locally produced wine and beer are just a few  staples for many Cascadian foodies here in Western Washington.

🌱Just sayin' y'all 🤷🤣😭🌱 Happy New Year 🎉

Recently, after getting really sick and running into complications I have decided to embrace what my family calls a "Porktarian Diet". Since the summer we have been experimenting with eating our normal raw foods diet but combined with pork at the end of the night. The reason we chose pork over other meats was because it has a richer complex of B-vitamins, higher than other meats, that help to calm down the nerves. 

Also, pigs are equal opportunists and will eat you as fast as you will eat them. Ask any experienced pig farmer & they will tell you never to pass out or fall asleep with a bunch of hogs. They will eat you alive. Google it if you don't want to take my word for it ;) Cows give us milk & chickens give us eggs - so we won't eat that meat. Anyways, my daughters and hubands health skyrocketed but I had my reservations and stopped the diet, going back to vegetarianism.

Then, I got hit with the flu. I haven't had the flu since highschool. It swelled up my eustachian tubes & created eustachian tube dysfunction. My right ear filled up with fluid, I lost hearing in my ear, and it was so painful I thought it was going to rupture. I was prescribed antibiotics that I ended up being allergic to and caused severe GI distress. I was put on more antibiotics and a probiotic but after the course, my ear still did not get better and my gut health was destroyed by the two antibiotics and severe reaction from the 1st course. I havent had an ear infection since I was a little kid!

Obviously, a vegetarian diet for me finally hit a wall. Despite going above and beyond with it. So here we are, eating a raw foods diet for breakfast, lunch, and any snacks (fruits, veggies, nuts, milk, cheese, dairy products, fermented foods). Then having raw food as an appetizer and a cooked dinner of pork. Since starting our "Porktatian" protocols for myself - I am getting stronger by the day and faster than I have eating a vegetatian diet. Hopefully, I have finally found the answer to a diet that works for our family both in health and preformance in sports.

🐔Why is there an egg shortage?!🐔

Here are the REAL reasons WHY egg prices are rising coming from someone who owns a registered farm & is in the industry. YES inflation, but why?

🐔Avian Flu: So far, there have been 60 million birds culled because of the influenza virus across 47 states, according to the USDA. 

🐔Avian flu has an easier time affecting egg layers rather than other breeds like Cornish Crosses or broiler chickens (meat chickens).

🐔Avian flu is spread by wildbirds especially water fowl. Therefore, it can decimate flocks faster than a blink of an eye.

🐔We have always HAD Avian flu, this year has just been the worst! As the virus is mutating.

🐔Businesses are being forced to pass on the higher costs to consumers. An avian flu that's wiped out egg-producing hens, leading to less hens laying eggs for consumers.

🐔Omicron is taking its toll at different levels of the supply chain. Warehouses, vendors, drivers, loaders— they call in sick. Which means egg deliveries are delayed.

🐔Feed cost has gone up. Pricey feed = pricey eggs. Contributing to the problem, less feed is getting to the chicken farmers because the Midwest growers are using corn to make an ethanol blend found at the gas pump.

🐔The war in 🇺🇦 is also be playing a part in the chicken and egg shortages, as both Russia and Ukraine are major producers of wheat and corn - a key ingredient in chicken feed.

🐔Rising egg prices and supply chain shortages have been exacerbated by the rising cost of oil, which is necessary for transportation. 

🐔#mjschookiefarm has been working tirelessly on biosecuirty practices & taking avian courses with the dept. of Agriculture. Our chickens are organic fed, free-ranged and pastured, and hand raised.

🌱Re-Post from @tin.foil.hat.farm 🌱I am NOT anti-vegan or anti-vegetarian. Your body your choice. However, I am anti-misinformation.

I WAS vegan and vegetarian for many, many, years. But there is a LOT of intentional misinformation and scare tactics that go on that is on the verge of brainwashing. It's political as much as it is commercial.

The truth is, you k*'ll 25 times more animals to produce the same amount of wheat protien as beef protien. Even organic soy farming k***s animals. And I have watched the crows follow the combines in Colorado and the seagulls/crows follow them here in Washington.

Once you step foot into animal and plant agriculture on a farm level (not hobby) you quickly realize first hand the truth of what really happens. 

When our family chose to start eating only pork (because we can get patured raised and pasture finished hog 10 minutes from our house that is dispatched humanely) experiencing the truth first hand is one of the many reasons we took that first step.

I realize how naive I was thinking that I took on less karma by having a farmer grow beans for my tofu. Yes, I acknowledged the fact that some animal d**th would happen. But I did not understand full scale, that it is actually more d**th than animal argiculture (not factory farm). 

This blow hit me hard the moment I started chicken farming and was awakened to the fact how the soy, corn, and wheat was being farmed for my chicken feed. In fact, chicken farming in general (even though we don't k*'ll our chickens for meat - they gives us eggs so I will never take their life for food) has made me realize how much we as humans are trying to escape our nature and distance ourselves from our ancestors.

One of the moments of realization was talking to our friend Mel who is from the Puyallup tribe. I was going on and on about how I couldn't handle the karma associated with k***ing animals. He looked me square in the eyes and said "What seperates us from the animals we eat?" Erik and I both looked at him. He pointed to his eyes. "Forward facing eyes. Just like other predators." He went on to talk about how all our ancestors regardless of race were all hunter gathers.

Flash backward to 2018 when Erik and I started our microfarm. Never in a million years did I believe I would become a chicken farmer too. But I never thought these two paths would intersect.

As there has been a war on drugs - now there is a global war on farmers.  Did you know?

🚜Today we have rapidly increasing food prices & shortage of supplies. Humanity is facing the worst hunger crisis the world has seen in decades. 

🚜Without farmers, the world would collapse. Farming is arguably the world’s most important profession. Right now, it’s under attack.

🚜“No Farmers, No Food,” outlines how the environmental activists are using the ploy of global warming to severely restrict the amount of chemical fertilizers and pesticides as well as the number of cattle which Dutch farmers can use and own. 

🚜Social media platforms with political agendas are censoring farmer accounts, deleting accounts, & pulling down posts of regenerative farming practices for "inciting violence".

🚜Misinformation in the form of half truths is pushing this agenda onto consumers. Who in turn, are trying to get farms shut down in the form of protesting.

🚜Rules are being passed to cut down livestock which in turn will result in farmers losing money & eventually the farm.

🚜 Regenerative farming is being lumped in with monocropping & feed lots. And then  No farmer wants that! We all want regenerative farming!

🌱My Kind of Burgers 🤤🌱 Y'all, hope you are having a great Feburary and start to Lent if you participate. I am nearing the end of my juice fast and have slowly been re-feeding with meat this week. Juice for Breakfast & Lunch with meat for dinner as part of the re-feeding plan. 

🎊This juice fast was amazing, because it did exactly what I needed it to do. All those biophotons helped streghthen my immune system and I did not get sick once while on this fast (even when a little kid coughed all over my face and I was surrounded by sick people). I feel amazing.

🍖For Lent, I decided to start the Carnivore diet. With no meat on Fridays. Wow, from Vegan/Vegetarian to that, right? The Carnivore diet is very restrictive allowing all meats, dairy, seafood, eggs, organ meats, bone marrow, & honey. I thought this would be a great sacrifice as I LOVE fruit & bread. 40 days without that is going to be BEYOND hard. Plus I wanted to continue the health reset on my body.

So many people have had amazing results that they didn't achieve through other diets like Paleo, Keto, Raw Vegan, or Veganism. Carnivore was the last bet, looking back to our ancestors for inspiration, when we ate a meat, organ, & fat centric diet.

🐤Black Copper Marans🐥 Much like cultivars, chicken breeds that are rare are much sought after. The Marans breed is an ancient breed from the south of France. While the origin of this breed is not well know they are thought to be an old type of landrace bird. What is a landrace? It is a local cultivar or animal breed that has been improved by traditional agricultural methods.

Black Copper Marans have spectacular plumage but their dark chocolate colored eggs are precisely what all the fuss is about. Eggs so dark that the bird often comes with a higher sticker price. Depending on egg darkness and lineage, it can cost you $10-$60 per chick. Although Marans are dual purpose chickens much like Wyandottes, all of the focus falls on their eggs. The eggs are said to taste like no other which is ideal if you are selling eggs. Not only do they add color but also refined taste.

These showstopping birds are docile, friendly, cold and heat hardy, do well in confinment and free range, some females carry the genetics to make speckles, are disease resistant, and they are great to work with children. Did you know there are many varieties of Marans? However, it is the Black Copper Marans who lay the darkest egg of them all. Did you also know the breed was named Marans after the French town they come from?  Which means even a single chicken is known as a Marans. And when pronouncing "marans" the "s" is silent. 

Black Copper Marans are considered rare in the United States but are more common in France. Just be sure to buy from a respectable and trusted breeder. Not all breeders are honest and may use a photo of dark eggs to sell their under performers. The Black Copper Marans all in all are a great addition to your flock!

Have you ever thought about a juice fast? Did you know the average person carries 20-25 lbs of fecal matter in the intestines?

Meat, dairy, eggs, and animal products pass quickly through our digestive system. But high fiber grains and plants take longer to digest. If you are going to eat grains, you need to soak and ferment them to take out anti-nutrients and phytates, but also so your body can pass it more quickly.

Fecal matter that stays in our system too long can make us very sick. It also can add a lot of weight to the body. The tell tale sign is often a bloated lower belly or puffiness under the sternum.

Going on a juice fast for 7 days to 30 days gets rid of this waste. It helps clean you out while also loading your body with biophotons, enzymes, minerals, and vitamins. It is like suler charging yout body and also giving your digestive system a break by clearning out impaction.

Did you know that spinach is very high in potassium and minerals? And that it also helps atophagy in cancer cells. However, it is a double edge sword. Spinach also has a very high amount of oxylates or crystals that can cause kidney or bladder stones.

So how do we reap the potassium without hurting our bodies with oxylates? The answer is calcium from animal-based foods. This binds with the oxylates and flushes them out of the body. So basically, you need a chaser - either bone broth, kefir, cheese, or yogurt.

What happens if we don't bind these crystals? Then they build up in our bodies and cause trouble. Kidney stones and bladder stones are examples of this! Therefore, stay safe and learn that #plantsaremedicine and #animalbaseddiet is food!

💀 Cleaning by burial 💀 Did you know you can clean deer bones by digging a 3ft hole or deeper and burying them? Classical European mounts, just the skull and antlers, use this method.

💀 The bones should stay buried up to a year. But it is useful if you can leave the bones exposed to the elements for a little bit before burying. This helps excellerate decomposition.

💀 Dig a hole at least 3ft deep and lay your bones or skulls in. Cover and pack tightly. And then place cinder blocks on top of the dig site to protect against predators.

💀 Once the bones are ready to be dug up, carefully remove them. Scrub them vigorously with dish soap and water. By a years time, all you have to do is take off the dirt.

💀 Once clean, you can leave the naturally stained bones if you like a natural forest look. Or go ahead and "bleach" the bones to get them white with oxyclean NOT actual bleach.

💀 If you don't want to wait this long there are a ton other methods. Using a biological, boiling, beetles, hydroxgen peroxide, bleach, or letting the elements strip the bones.

💀 We got this 4-point buck from the side of the road. Unfourtantley, he got hit by a car in our neighborhood. Someone beat us to the meat, but we were able to collect the legs, some thigh bones, and 1 antler (the other one got shattered by the accident). Will make for some nice decoration pieces 🙃
